OL,6,FIt notes the charge should only be
OL,7,Frecorded "where widespread damage is
OL,8,Fcaused, where the value of the damage
OL,9,Fis considerable, or where there is
OL,10,Fdisruption of power supply, flooding
OL,11,For similar".
OL,13,FThe publication states there is no
OL,14,Fspecific financial value where a
OL,15,Fpotential crime would be recorded as
OL,16,Fmalicious mischief rather than
OL,17,Fvandalism but multiple thousands of
OL,18,Fpounds of alleged damage would be
OL,19,Frequired for it to be recorded as the
OL,20,Fformer.
